AB  - To water quality management of the Gotvand Reservoir, this paper attempts to determine to what extent the negative impacts of Anbar salt domes dissolution can be reduced considering releasing water from different levels of the dam reservoir. In this respect, the required field data at Gotvand Reservoir site were collected and hydrodynamic simulation of the reservoir as well as salt karst dissolution process were performed from August, 2011 to March, 2017 by system dynamics method and using the Vensim software. The SD model analysis results showed that the amount of salt stored was about 69 million tons and salt dissolution coefficient value during the simulation period varies between 98 and 339.5 kg/s. This variation for the salt karst corrosion is 4.7-7.4 cm/day. Also, by Dewatering from levels above the level of lower gates (149.5 m on average) can decline the salinity of the released water by 85.3%. Moreover, the most important factor in salt karst dissolution was the water surface elevation in the reservoir. therefore, it can be concluded that by controlling the amount of water flowing into the Gotvand Dam's reservoir via controlling the amount of water flowing out of the Dez Dam, situated on the upstream of the Gotvand Dam, and by controlling the amount of water flowing out of the Gotvand Dam's reservoir, and to put it differently, by implementing the optimum rule curves for the Gotvand Dam and the Dez Dam, the salinity of the water flowing out of the Gotvand Dam's reservoir can be largely reduced.
