AB  - Under the "Dual Carbon" targets, resource-rich regions face the dual challenges of renewable energy integration and environmental pollution control, while the evolution of renewable energy (RE) and coal coupled systems brings transformative pressures to traditional coal mining and power generation sectors. This study constructs an integrated RE-coal coupled system by deeply synergizing regional renewable and coal resources across industrial chains. Employing system dynamics theory, we elucidate cross-sector interaction mechanisms and feedback loops, develop a dynamic model simulated via Vensim, and quantitatively assess its economic benefits. The findings indicate that the green hydrogen-anchored coupling system exhibits both economic viability with an annual profit of 10 billion CNY and technical feasibility with a carbon dioxide reduction of 1.36 million tons. By leveraging the regional advantages of low-cost renewable energy and abundant coal resources, this model decouples economic growth from carbon emissions, providing an implementable pathway for renewable energy and coal-rich regions to fulfill their 2030 carbon peak commitments.
