AB  - The System Dynamics is emerging as an alternative to the traditional techniques of information analysis, since it permits to analyze and synthesize different structural causes that promote the behavior of interest. However, this involves raising awareness on the role of each element and how different actions carried out on parts of it, accentuate or attenuate the trend implicit in it (Garcia, 2007).
   Taking this aspects Into consideration, this article presents the first version of the model to be developed within the research project "Model Market Access to Broadband Internet Service to Residential, an Approach from the System Dynamics", in which the different elements present in the market will be considered, and a simulation of their behavior will be conducted, using the Vensim PLE version 5.8c (2007) software, designed to work under the focus of system dynamics.
