AB  - The problem of information asymmetry has become the main reason for the inefficiency of the closed-loop supply chain (CLSC). This article is based on the idea of cloud manufacturing and provides a framework for information exchange and sharing between various entities in the form of distributed networking. With the participation of the government, the research on the information-sharing enthusiasm of remanufacturers and recyclers in CLSC and its influencing factors is combined with evolutionary game theory and system dynamics. Under the premise of bounded rationality, a tripartite evolutionary game model is constructed, and equilibrium analysis is carried out. On this basis, based on the principles of system dynamics, Vensim is used to simulate the evolutionary game process dynamically, and the influence of parameter changes on information-sharing enthusiasm and strategy selection is discussed. In addition, a closed-loop supply chain SD model in cloud environment is established to prove its role in information sharing. The research results show that the strategic choices of CLSC members are affected by multiple external variables. Factors such as government supervision, sharing costs, information security, and enterprise alliances play a key role in companies adopting cloud manufacturing models for remanufacturing activities.
